Slide 1: Title
- Detecting Audio Deepfakes: AASIST v3 + Explainability
- UVA × Capital One Capstone — eglhannah / Arnav Jain et al.
- Repo: eglhannah/CapitalOne_AudioDeepfake_Project

Slide 2: Problem & Motivation
- Voice-biometrics spoofing risk
- TTS/VC/DeepFake threats to ASV
- Need for robust countermeasures + explainability

Slide 3: Benchmark / Data Context (ASVspoof)
- Datasets: 2019 LA (training), 2021 LA eval (telephony codecs), 2021 DF eval (media compression)
- Scale: 2019_eval ~71K utts; 2021_LA ~148K; 2021_DF ~534K
- Attack diversity: 2019 (A01–A19); 2021 DF (100+ systems)

Slide 4: AASIST Model & Reference
- Architecture: AASIST pipeline → 128-d pooled embedding → classifier head
- Local files: aasist/code/train_aasist_v3.py, simple_aasist.py

Slide 5: Version History & Headline Results
- v1 baseline: 2019_dev 0.90% EER; 2021_DF 22.95%
- v2 RawBoost: improved many metrics; 2021_DF -> 17.20%

Slide 6: v3 Goal & Approach
- Goal: close 2021_DF gap (target <15% EER)
- Approach: codec-realistic augmentation (ffmpeg round-trips)
- Files: aasist/code/train_aasist_v3.py, sbatch_aasist_v3.sh

Slide 7: Training & Evaluation Pipeline
- Scripts: aasist/code/*.py and sbatch_*.sh
- Checkpoint path noted in aasist/README.md (not in git)
- Typical compute: ~3 hr on NVIDIA A6000

Slide 8: Explainability — interpret_aasist_shap.py
- Three levels: embedding-level SHAP, temporal occlusion/audio SHAP, spectrogram surrogate SHAP
- Outputs written to interpretation_results/ (plots + CSVs)
- Usage (schematic): python interpret_aasist_shap.py --data_dir <flac_dir> --protocol <trl.txt> --device cuda

Slide 9: Key Explainability Outputs to Show
- embedding_importance.csv, sample_explanations.csv, occlusion_sensitivity.csv
- Plots: embedding_importance_bar.png, spectrogram_shap_aggregate.png, temporal_importance_overview.png, correct_vs_incorrect.png

Slide 10: Next Steps & Summary
- Run v3 training with codec augmentation
- Run interpret pipeline before/after v3 to compare embedding importance and spectrogram SHAP
- Contacts: Arnav Jain (owner), Hannah (explainability)

